Package com.verisign.epp.codec.reseller

Class Summary
EPPResellerAddress Represents a reseller address.
EPPResellerCheckCmd Represents a reseller <check> command that enables checking on the availability of a set of client-specified but server-unique reseller identifiers.
EPPResellerCheckResp Represents a reseller <check> response that returns the availability of a set of client-specified but server-unique reseller identifiers.
EPPResellerCheckResult EPPResellerCheckResult is used to represent the for the check of an individual reseller.
EPPResellerContact Represents a reseller contact.
EPPResellerCreateCmd Command used to create a reseller object.
EPPResellerCreateResp Represents an EPP Internationalized Domain Name (IDN) Table <info> response, which support three different forms:
Domain Info Form - Used to validate the domain name code points against the IDN Tables and IDN Policies, and to return the matching IDN Table meta-data.
EPPResellerDeleteCmd Command used to delete a reseller object.
EPPResellerDisclose Represents a reseller disclose definition.
EPPResellerInfoCmd Command used to retrieve information associated with a reseller object.
EPPResellerInfoResp Represents an EPP Internationalized Domain Name (IDN) Table <info> response, which support three different forms:
Domain Info Form - Used to validate the domain name code points against the IDN Tables and IDN Policies, and to return the matching IDN Table meta-data.
EPPResellerMapFactory Factory for the Reseller Mapping command and response objects.
EPPResellerPostalDefinition Represents a reseller postal address definition.
EPPResellerTst Is a unit test of the com.verisign.epp.codec.reseller package.
EPPResellerUpdateCmd Command used to update a reseller object.
 

Enum Summary
EPPResellerContact.Type Contact type enumeration.
EPPResellerDisclose.Type Localized type with one of the following values:
LOC - Localized form of data that MAY be represented in unrestricted UTF-8.
EPPResellerPostalDefinition.Type Localized type with one of the following values:
LOC - Localized form of data that MAY be represented in unrestricted UTF-8.
State Operational state of the reseller, with one of the following values:
OK - The normal status value for the reseller object.
